<TITLE> Brothers lick Khulna Abahani 3-1 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Khulna, Sept 22 (bdnews24.com) - Favorites Brothers Union recorded a 3-1 away win over Khulna Abahani Krira Chakra in the Citycell B. League at Khulna Stadium Monday. Chibuike Divine, Mehdi Hasan Tapu and Ashraful Kader Manju scored one goal each for the Gopibagh-based outfit, that made a 1-1 draw against Chittagong Mohammedan Sporting Club in their first match at Bangabandhu National Stadium. Mehdi Hasan, who struck twice in their 3-1 win over struggling Muktijoddha Sangsad, scored the lone goal for Khulna Abahani. The Nigerian striker, Divine, put Brothers ahead in the 17th minute converting a penalty shot before his strike pair Tapu doubled the margin in the 73rd minute. One minute later, Mehdi Hasan reduced the Abahani margin when he struck his league's third goal, but Manju sealed the match to give Brothers its first win in the second match. With the first triumph, Brothers joined Dhaka Mohammedan SC, Sheikh Russel KC and Chittagong Abahani Ltd on the top of the points table with four points each from two matches. Abahani remained on their previous three points from two games. bdnew
